acpi: thermal: retain downstream hwmon, power and sensor fixes

Preserve each ACPI thermal zone's bus ID as its thermal-core type.  Use an
independent "acpitz" hwmon type to group the labelled readings under one
adapter.  This keeps unique types available to thermal APIs, sysfs,
netlink, and tracing without sacrificing readable sensors output.

Treat SSTP as an optional power-allocation hint.  Make the optional SPRG
and DPRG power lookups return zero deterministically when firmware omits
them.  Reject affinity index 12 as out of range for the twelve Sky1 CPUs.

